Samsung IR Remote Control Signal Dumps
======================================

This directory contains Consumer Infrared (CIR) signal dumps from Samsung
remote controls. Samsung uses a proprietary IR protocol for their devices.

Samsung IR Protocol Details:
-----------------------------
- Carrier frequency: 38 kHz
- Modulation: Pulse distance coding
- Start pulse: ~4.5ms high, ~4.5ms low
- Logic '1': ~560μs high, ~1.69ms low
- Logic '0': ~560μs high, ~560μs low
- Data format: 32 bits (8-bit address + 8-bit command + 16-bit checksum)

Files:
------
- samsung_tv_power.sr: Power button press
- samsung_tv_volume_up.sr: Volume up button press
- samsung_tv_channel_up.sr: Channel up button press
- samsung_tv_menu.sr: Menu button press
- samsung_tv_numbers.sr: Number buttons 0-9

Equipment:
----------
- Remote: Samsung BN59-01175N (or similar)
- Target: Samsung Smart TV
- Capture device: Logic analyzer at 1 MHz sample rate
- IR receiver: TSOP4838 or similar 38 kHz IR receiver

Notes:
------
These dumps demonstrate the Samsung proprietary IR protocol which is different
from standard NEC, RC5, or RC6 protocols. The protocol includes error detection
and repeat codes for held buttons.
